Joan Virginia O'Hara has been nominated to be the Executive Secretary of the National Security Council. She has previously served as the Principal Deputy Executive Secretary and Deputy Chief of Staff of the National Security Council. O'Hara has also worked as the Deputy National Security Advisor and Acting National Security Advisor to Vice President Mike Pence. Prior to joining the White House, she served in the House Homeland Security Committee. O'Hara holds a B.A. from Loyola College, an M.A. from San Diego State University-California State University, and a J.D., cum laude, from New York Law School.